FBIS3-17658 "drsov060_m_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 Tajikistan Opposition Said Preparing Attacks on Russian Guards LD2803151094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1412 GMT 28 Mar 94 LD2803151094 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tajikistan's armed opposition is preparing to subject Russian-manned posts on one of the sections of the republic's border with Afghanistan to mortar attacks in response to a stepping-up of measures to secure that stretch of the border, the press bureau of the Russian border guards in Tajiikistan told INTERFAX. In some areas along that part of the border, which is close to the town of Khorog, the opposition also plans to lay mines made of explosives stolen from state storehouses, the bureau said. It said the border guard command had launched a set of measures to ensure the safety of troops and stabilize the situation on the Khorog section of the border.
